Some patients developed shortness of breath and/or reduced tissue oxygenation a week after the onset of the disease.
In severe cases, symptoms of acute respiratory syndrome, infectious shock, metabolic acidosis and blood clotting disorder were observed in patients.
Patients with fever and/or respiratory symptoms and severe fever, even if they do not have abnormalities in the bladder imaging, should be screened for rapid virus detection.
